The paper proposes a monocular visual-inertial SLAM system that performs relocalization and global optimization to correct drifts and achieve global consistency. This involves techniques related to robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
